# Illustrative environment for the docs' deployment worked examples — every value a
# placeholder, never a real credential.
#
# A deployment TOML never holds a secret value; it holds a secret REFERENCE, and the
# `[env]NAME` scheme dereferences the environment variable NAME at compose time
# (docs/components/deployment/reference.md § Secret references). An unset or empty
# variable fails loudly at compose — there is no fallback value.
#
# The variable names below are the ones the docs' worked examples use:
#   api_key_ref  = "[env]LLM_PROD_KEY"       (trainable transport examples)
#   webhook_ref  = "[env]WEBHOOK_DEV_TOKEN"  (deployment reference example)
#   auth_header_ref = "[env]WEBHOOK_TOKEN"   (handler reference example)
LLM_PROD_KEY=sk-example-not-a-real-key
WEBHOOK_DEV_TOKEN=example-dev-webhook-token
WEBHOOK_TOKEN=example-webhook-token
